{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1721,"text":"I have a confession to make."},{"time":4181,"text":"I am addicted to adventure,"},{"time":7420,"text":"and as a young boy,"},{"time":9859,"text":"I would rather look outside the window"},{"time":12367,"text":"at the birds in the trees and the sky"},{"time":15101,"text":"than looking at that two-dimensional"},{"time":17237,"text":"chalky blackboard where time stands still"},{"time":21208,"text":"and even sometimes dies."},{"time":23953,"text":"My teachers thought there was something wrong"},{"time":25763,"text":"with me because I wasn't paying attention in class."},{"time":29150,"text":"They didn't find anything \nspecifically wrong with me,"},{"time":31170,"text":"other than being slightly \ndyslexic because I'm a lefty."},{"time":35692,"text":"But they didn't test for curiosity."},{"time":39807,"text":"Curiosity, to me,"},{"time":42388,"text":"is about our connection"},{"time":44361,"text":"with the world, with the universe."},{"time":47606,"text":"It's about seeing what's \naround that next coral head"},{"time":49496,"text":"or what's around that next tree,"},{"time":51195,"text":"and learning more not only about our environment"},{"time":53254,"text":"but about ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55324,"text":"Now, my dream of dreams,"},{"time":57854,"text":"I want to go explore the oceans of Mars,"},{"time":61128,"text":"but until we can go there,"},{"time":63974,"text":"I think the oceans still hold"},{"time":67440,"text":"quite a few secrets."},{"time":68879,"text":"As a matter of fact,"},{"time":70243,"text":"if you take our planet as the oasis in space that it is"},{"time":73798,"text":"and dissect it into a living space,"},{"time":77429,"text":"the ocean represents over 3.4 billion"},{"time":80824,"text":"cubic kilometers of volume, within which"},{"time":83311,"text":"we've explored less than five percent."},{"time":87821,"text":"And I look at this, and I go, well,"},{"time":90080,"text":"there are tools to go \ndeeper, longer and further:"},{"time":93446,"text":"submarines, ROVs, even Scuba diving."},{"time":98659,"text":"But if we're going to explore the final frontier"},{"time":101267,"text":"on this planet, we need to live there."},{"time":104754,"text":"We need to build a log cabin, if you will,"},{"time":107352,"text":"at the bottom of the sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110412,"text":"And so there was a great curiosity in my soul"},{"time":113378,"text":"when I went to go visit a TED [Prize winner]"},{"time":116145,"text":"by the name of Dr. Sylvia Earle."},{"time":117580,"text":"Maybe you've heard of her."},{"time":119064,"text":"Two years ago, she was staked out"},{"time":122840,"text":"at the last undersea marine laboratory"},{"time":125684,"text":"to try and save it,"},{"time":127667,"text":"to try and petition"},{"time":129355,"text":"for us not to scrap it"},{"time":131145,"text":"and bring it back on land."},{"time":133546,"text":"We've only had about a dozen or so"},{"time":135458,"text":"scientific labs at the bottom of the sea."},{"time":137888,"text":"There's only one left in the world:"},{"time":139800,"text":"it's nine miles offshore"},{"time":141021,"text":"and 65 feet down."},{"time":143355,"text":"It's called Aquarius."},{"time":145010,"text":"Aquarius, in some fashion,"},{"time":147382,"text":"is a dinosaur,"},{"time":149631,"text":"an ancient robot chained to the bottom,"},{"time":151971,"text":"this Leviathan."},{"time":155391,"text":"In other ways, it's a legacy."},{"time":157546,"text":"And so with that visit, I realized \nthat my time is short"},{"time":160430,"text":"if I wanted to experience"},{"time":162681,"text":"what it was like to become an aquanaut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167708,"text":"When we swam towards this after many"},{"time":170194,"text":"moons of torture and two years of preparation,"},{"time":172940,"text":"this habitat waiting to invite us"},{"time":177909,"text":"was like a new home."},{"time":180925,"text":"And the point of going down to"},{"time":183120,"text":"and living at this habitat was not to stay inside."},{"time":186967,"text":"It wasn't about living at something\nthe size of a school bus."},{"time":189566,"text":"It was about giving us the luxury of time"},{"time":192772,"text":"outside to wander, to explore,"},{"time":195821,"text":"to understand more about this oceanic final frontier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199704,"text":"We had megafauna come and visit us."},{"time":202011,"text":"This spotted eagle ray is a fairly\ncommon sight in the oceans."},{"time":205551,"text":"But why this is so important,"},{"time":208183,"text":"why this picture is up,"},{"time":209758,"text":"is because this particular animal\nbrought his friends around,"},{"time":213223,"text":"and instead of being the\npelagic animals that they were,"},{"time":216370,"text":"they started getting curious about us,"},{"time":217760,"text":"these new strangers that were\nmoving into the neighborhood,"},{"time":221749,"text":"doing things with plankton."},{"time":224268,"text":"We were studying all sorts of animals and critters,"},{"time":226970,"text":"and they got closer and closer to us,"},{"time":229457,"text":"and because of the luxury of time,"},{"time":231239,"text":"these animals, these residents of the coral reef,"},{"time":233590,"text":"were starting to get used to us,"},{"time":235004,"text":"and these pelagics that\nnormal travel through stopped."},{"time":238681,"text":"This particular animal actually circled"},{"time":241184,"text":"for 31 full days during our mission."},{"time":245335,"text":"So mission 31 wasn't so much"},{"time":247675,"text":"about breaking records."},{"time":249587,"text":"It was about that human-ocean connection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254021,"text":"Because of the luxury of time, we were able"},{"time":256175,"text":"to study animals such as sharks and grouper"},{"time":260134,"text":"in aggregations that we've never seen before."},{"time":262384,"text":"It's like seeing dogs and \ncats behaving well together."},{"time":266970,"text":"Even being able to commune with animals"},{"time":268745,"text":"that are much larger than us,"},{"time":269872,"text":"such as this endangered goliath grouper"},{"time":272634,"text":"who only still resides in the Florida Keys."},{"time":275896,"text":"Of course, just like any neighbor,"},{"time":278205,"text":"after a while, if they get tired,"},{"time":280725,"text":"the goliath grouper barks at us,"},{"time":282345,"text":"and this bark is so powerful"},{"time":284141,"text":"that it actually stuns its prey before it aspirates it all"},{"time":286800,"text":"within a split second."},{"time":288769,"text":"For us, it's just telling us to go back"},{"time":290286,"text":"into the habitat and leave them alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294918,"text":"Now, this wasn't just about adventure."},{"time":298149,"text":"There was actually a serious note to it."},{"time":299978,"text":"We did a lot of science, and again,\nbecause of the luxury of time,"},{"time":303279,"text":"we were able to do over three years of science"},{"time":305845,"text":"in 31 days."},{"time":308306,"text":"In this particular case, we were using a PAM,"},{"time":310522,"text":"or, let me just see if I can get this straight,"},{"time":312243,"text":"a Pulse Amplitude Modulated Fluorometer."},{"time":316262,"text":"And our scientists from FIU, MIT,"},{"time":319465,"text":"and from Northeastern"},{"time":321520,"text":"were able to get a gauge for what coral reefs do"},{"time":324493,"text":"when we're not around."},{"time":326181,"text":"The Pulse Amplitude Modulated\nFluorometer, or PAM,"},{"time":328734,"text":"gauges the fluorescence of corals"},{"time":331240,"text":"as it pertains to pollutants in the water"},{"time":333717,"text":"as well as climate change-related issues."},{"time":337103,"text":"We used all sorts of other cutting-edge tools,"},{"time":340601,"text":"such as this sonde, or what I like to call"},{"time":342930,"text":"the sponge proctologist, whereby the sonde"},{"time":349084,"text":"itself tests for metabolism rates"},{"time":351887,"text":"in what in this particular case is a barrel sponge,"},{"time":354987,"text":"or the redwoods of the [ocean]."},{"time":357338,"text":"And this gives us a much better gauge"},{"time":358610,"text":"of what's happening underwater"},{"time":360928,"text":"with regard to climate change-related issues,"},{"time":363863,"text":"and how the dynamics of that"},{"time":365651,"text":"affect us here on land."},{"time":368261,"text":"And finally, we looked at predator-prey behavior."},{"time":370743,"text":"And predator-prey behavior is an interesting thing,"},{"time":372671,"text":"because as we take away some of the predators"},{"time":375168,"text":"on these coral reefs around the world,"},{"time":377339,"text":"the prey, or the forage fish, act very differently."},{"time":380904,"text":"What we realized is"},{"time":382558,"text":"not only do they stop taking care of the reef,"},{"time":385741,"text":"darting in, grabbing a little bit of algae"},{"time":387665,"text":"and going back into their homes,"},{"time":389184,"text":"they start spreading out and disappearing"},{"time":391163,"text":"from those particular coral reefs."},{"time":393278,"text":"Well, within that 31 days,"},{"time":395606,"text":"we were able to generate over 10 scientific papers"},{"time":398295,"text":"on each one of these topics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401426,"text":"But the point of adventure is not only to learn,"},{"time":406132,"text":"it's to be able to share that \nknowledge with the world,"},{"time":408525,"text":"and with that, thanks to a \ncouple of engineers at MIT,"},{"time":412507,"text":"we were able to use a prototype\ncamera called the Edgertronic"},{"time":415840,"text":"to capture slow-motion video,"},{"time":418901,"text":"up to 20,000 frames per second"},{"time":421673,"text":"in a little box"},{"time":423052,"text":"that's worth 3,000 dollars."},{"time":424693,"text":"It's available to every one of us."},{"time":426937,"text":"And that particular camera gives us an insight"},{"time":429655,"text":"into what fairly common animals do"},{"time":432280,"text":"but we can't even see it in the blink of an eye."},{"time":434526,"text":"Let me show you a quick video"},{"time":436836,"text":"of what this camera does."},{"time":438906,"text":"You can see the silky bubble come out"},{"time":441741,"text":"of our hard hats."},{"time":443920,"text":"It gives us an insight"},{"time":446252,"text":"into some of the animals that we were sitting"},{"time":448613,"text":"right next to for 31 days"},{"time":450571,"text":"and never normally would have paid attention to,"},{"time":453280,"text":"such as hermit crabs."},{"time":455160,"text":"Now, using a cutting-edge piece of technology"},{"time":458175,"text":"that's not really meant for the oceans"},{"time":460300,"text":"is not always easy."},{"time":462444,"text":"We sometimes had to put the camera upside down,"},{"time":464992,"text":"cordon it back to the lab,"},{"time":467552,"text":"and actually man the trigger"},{"time":470073,"text":"from the lab itself."},{"time":472247,"text":"But what this gives us"},{"time":474441,"text":"is the foresight to look at and analyze"},{"time":477275,"text":"in scientific and engineering terms"},{"time":480482,"text":"some of the most amazing behavior"},{"time":483646,"text":"that the human eye just can't pick up,"},{"time":484901,"text":"such as this manta shrimp"},{"time":487950,"text":"trying to catch its prey,"},{"time":489718,"text":"within about .3 seconds."},{"time":495217,"text":"That punch is as strong as a .22 caliber bullet,"},{"time":498312,"text":"and if you ever try to catch a bullet"},{"time":499657,"text":"in mid-flight with your eye, impossible."},{"time":503675,"text":"But now we can see things"},{"time":504978,"text":"such as these Christmas tree worms"},{"time":507648,"text":"pulling in and fanning out"},{"time":510809,"text":"in a way that the eye just can't capture,"},{"time":513845,"text":"or in this case,"},{"time":515219,"text":"a fish throwing up grains of sand."},{"time":522280,"text":"This is an actual sailfin goby,"},{"time":524670,"text":"and if you look at it in real time,"},{"time":527186,"text":"it actually doesn't even show its fanning motion"},{"time":530191,"text":"because it's so quick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533362,"text":"One of the most precious gifts\nthat we had underwater"},{"time":535634,"text":"is that we had WiFi,"},{"time":537974,"text":"and for 31 days straight we were able to connect"},{"time":540190,"text":"with the world in real time \nfrom the bottom of the sea"},{"time":542903,"text":"and share all of these experiences."},{"time":544735,"text":"Quite literally right there"},{"time":546160,"text":"I am Skyping in the classroom"},{"time":547306,"text":"with one of the six continents"},{"time":549324,"text":"and some of the 70,000 \nstudents that we connected"},{"time":552280,"text":"every single day to some of these experiences."},{"time":555070,"text":"As a matter of fact, I'm showing a picture that I took"},{"time":557333,"text":"with my smartphone from underwater"},{"time":559977,"text":"of a goliath grouper laying on the bottom."},{"time":562508,"text":"We had never seen that before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567532,"text":"And I dream of the day"},{"time":569349,"text":"that we have underwater cities,"},{"time":571844,"text":"and maybe, just maybe, if we push the boundaries"},{"time":574409,"text":"of adventure and knowledge,"},{"time":576343,"text":"and we share that knowledge with others out there,"},{"time":579584,"text":"we can solve all sorts of problems."},{"time":582731,"text":"My grandfather used to say,"},{"time":584189,"text":"\"People protect what they love.\""},{"time":587142,"text":"My father, \"How can people protect"},{"time":589741,"text":"what they don't understand?\""},{"time":594665,"text":"And I've thought about this my whole life."},{"time":598706,"text":"Nothing is impossible."},{"time":602014,"text":"We need to dream, we need to be creative,"},{"time":605197,"text":"and we all need to have an adventure"},{"time":607570,"text":"in order to create miracles in the darkest of times."},{"time":611221,"text":"And whether it's about climate change"},{"time":613858,"text":"or eradicating poverty"},{"time":616355,"text":"or giving back to future generations"},{"time":617998,"text":"what we've taken for granted,"},{"time":620596,"text":"it's about adventure."},{"time":622610,"text":"And who knows, maybe\nthere will be underwater cities,"},{"time":625298,"text":"and maybe some of you"},{"time":626380,"text":"will become the future aquanauts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628988,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630866,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}